
# MySQL Practice Repository

Welcome to the MySQL Practice Repository  
This repository is maintained by [shovo896](https://github.com/shovo896) and is intended for learning, practicing, and  demonstrating all key concepts of MySQL through real-world examples and SQL scripts.

---

## Repo Structure


mysql
│
├── basic\_commands.sql          -- Basic SQL syntax: SELECT, INSERT, DELETE, UPDATE
├── joins.sql                   -- INNER JOIN, LEFT JOIN, RIGHT JOIN, FULL OUTER JOIN
├── subqueries.sql              -- Subqueries, nested SELECTs, correlated subqueries
├── views\_and\_indexes.sql       -- Creating and managing views and indexes
├── triggers.sql                -- BEFORE/AFTER INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE triggers
├── procedures\_and\_functions.sql-- Stored procedures and user-defined functions
├── transactions.sql            -- COMMIT, ROLLBACK, SAVEPOINT
├── constraints.sql             -- Primary, Foreign, Unique, Check constraints
├── full\_course\_summary.sql     -- Full MySQL course in a single 300+ line script
└── README.md                   -- Documentation (this file)


---

##  Topics Covered

✅ Database creation and basic DDL  
✅ Data types and constraints  
✅ SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE  
✅ Aggregate functions, GROUP BY, HAVING  
✅ Subqueries and nested queries  
✅ Views and Indexes  
✅ Stored Procedures & Functions  
✅ Triggers (Before/After)  
✅ Transactions and rollback  
✅ All types of Joins  
✅ Full SQL course script

---

##  Getting Started

### Requirements
- MySQL Server (version 8.0+ recommended)
- MySQL Workbench / CLI / phpMyAdmin
  
### Running the SQL Files
1. Clone this repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/shovo896/my_sql.git
````

2. Open your preferred MySQL client.
3. Load and run the `.sql` files one by one.
4. Make sure the database used in each script is created and selected with `USE`.


## Learning Goal

This repository is ideal for:

* Students preparing for SQL exams/interviews
* Developers brushing up MySQL skills
* Beginners who want practical scripts
* Anyone who wants to revise full MySQL course with examples

